fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.gui

Class ExplorerGui<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.gui.GuiBase
      • fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.gui.InventoryGui
        • fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.gui.ActionGui
          • fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.gui.ExplorerGui<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of data this GUI will display.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayPromptGui

    public abstract class ExplorerGui<T>
extends ActionGui
    This class implements an exploration GUI, allowing users to see a set of data in a paginated view, and to manipulate it or get it (if the creative mode is enabled for this GUI â€” enabled by default).

    This GUI supports both one- and two-dimensional contents; two-dimensional content is represented by a one-dimension list and a width, or by getViewItem(int, int) if you override it (in this case you need to call setDataShape(int, int) in the ActionGui.onUpdate() method).

    Author:
    ProkopyL and Amaury Carrade

      • onPutItem

        protected boolean onPutItem(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item)
        Triggered when the player tries to place an item inside the GUI.

        This will not place the item in the GUI, it's up to you to update the data and refresh the GUI if you need so.

        Parameters:
        item - The ItemStack the player is trying to put.
        Returns:
        false to cancel the placement; true to accept it.

      • setKeepHorizontalScrollingSpace

        public void setKeepHorizontalScrollingSpace(boolean keepHorizontalScrollingSpace)
        If set to true, the horizontal scrolling line will remain empty even without scrolls (with one page typically), so you can place buttons or things like that in this area.

        Else, with one page, the place will be used to display an additional row of data.

        Parameters:
        keepHorizontalScrollingSpace - true if enabled.

      • setKeepVerticalScrollingSpace

        public void setKeepVerticalScrollingSpace(boolean keepVerticalScrollingSpace)
        If set to true, the vertical scrolling line will remain empty even without scrolls (with one page typically), so you can place buttons or things like that in this area.

        Else, with one page, the place will be used to display an additional column of data.

        Parameters:
        keepVerticalScrollingSpace - true if enabled.
